{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RPqWKZqYVUhjpxZNBA9Uiu","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Here are the full contents of the fairness package files:\n\n## Summary\n\nThe commitment algorithm is straightforward:\n\n**Commitment = SHA256(serverSeed)**\n\nWhere:\n- **Input**: `serverSeed` (hex string, 64 chars = 32 bytes)\n- **Process**: Convert hex string to bytes → SHA256 hash → Convert back to hex string\n- **Output**: 64-character hex string\n\n### Key Implementation Details\n\n**commitment.ts:**\n- `computeCommitment(serverSeed)`: Takes a hex string, converts to bytes via `hexToBytes()`, hashes with `sha256()`, returns as hex via `bytesToHex()`\n- `verifyCommitment(serverSeed, commitment)`: Recomputes the commitment and compares case-insensitively\n\n**crash.ts:**\n- For crash games, uses **HMAC-SHA256** with the server seed as the key:\n  - Message: `publicSeed:roundId:gameId`\n  - Hash: `HMAC-SHA256(serverSeedBytes, messageBytes)`\n  - Takes first 52 bits (13 hex chars) and applies formula to get crash multiplier (1.0x+)\n\n**verification.ts:**\n- `verifyRound()` checks:\n  1. Server seed matches the commitment (via `verifyCommitment`)\n  2. Computed outcome matches claimed outcome (with 0.01 tolerance)\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `@noble/hashes` v1.6.0 (cryptographic hashing)\n\n**Test Coverage:**\n- SHA256 of zero byte validates against known constant\n- Determinism verified\n- Different seeds produce different commitments\n- Case-insensitive verification\n\nAll files are located in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: afcef4a94529fd025 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 35059\ntool_uses: 7\nduration_ms: 36079</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f4316b62-2257-4469-b202-66365945525c","uuid":"995b7203-bb57-46ec-b6f0-8f8dc0ed4cd9","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the following files and return their full contents:\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts` — the existing commitment/verification functions\n2. Any other .ts files in `sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/` \n3. `sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/package.json`\n\nI need to understand the exact commitment algorithm (sha256 of what exactly?) and how it's implemented.","agentId":"afcef4a94529fd025","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Here are the full contents of the fairness package files:\n\n## Summary\n\nThe commitment algorithm is straightforward:\n\n**Commitment = SHA256(serverSeed)**\n\nWhere:\n- **Input**: `serverSeed` (hex string, 64 chars = 32 bytes)\n- **Process**: Convert hex string to bytes → SHA256 hash → Convert back to hex string\n- **Output**: 64-character hex string\n\n### Key Implementation Details\n\n**commitment.ts:**\n- `computeCommitment(serverSeed)`: Takes a hex string, converts to bytes via `hexToBytes()`, hashes with `sha256()`, returns as hex via `bytesToHex()`\n- `verifyCommitment(serverSeed, commitment)`: Recomputes the commitment and compares case-insensitively\n\n**crash.ts:**\n- For crash games, uses **HMAC-SHA256** with the server seed as the key:\n  - Message: `publicSeed:roundId:gameId`\n  - Hash: `HMAC-SHA256(serverSeedBytes, messageBytes)`\n  - Takes first 52 bits (13 hex chars) and applies formula to get crash multiplier (1.0x+)\n\n**verification.ts:**\n- `verifyRound()` checks:\n  1. Server seed matches the commitment (via `verifyCommitment`)\n  2. Computed outcome matches claimed outcome (with 0.01 tolerance)\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `@noble/hashes` v1.6.0 (cryptographic hashing)\n\n**Test Coverage:**\n- SHA256 of zero byte validates against known constant\n- Determinism verified\n- Different seeds produce different commitments\n- Case-insensitive verification\n\nAll files are located in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/`"}],"totalDurationMs":36079,"tota