{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UfhKew8eGwXTTEynqzJnCg","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information needed. Let me compile the findings:\n\n## CoinflipMatch PDA Derivation - Complete Reference\n\n### On-Chain Definition (Rust)\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs` (lines 18-19)\n\n```rust\n/// A coinflip match between two players (commit-reveal model).\n/// PDA seeds: [b\"match\", creator.key().as_ref(), &nonce.to_le_bytes()]\n#[account]\n#[derive(InitSpace)]\npub struct CoinflipMatch { ... }\n```\n\n**Seed Format (Exact)**:\n```\n[\"match\", creator, nonce.to_le_bytes()]\n```\n\nWhere:\n- `\"match\"` = UTF-8 bytes `[109, 97, 116, 99, 104]`\n- `creator` = PublicKey (32 bytes)\n- `nonce` = u64 in little-endian format (8 bytes)\n\n---\n\n### TypeScript PDA Derivation\n\n**Primary Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` (lines 38-45)\n\n```typescript\nexport function getMatchPda(creator: PublicKey, nonce: bigint | number): [PublicKey, number] {\n  const nonceBuf = Buffer.alloc(8);\n  nonceBuf.writeBigUInt64LE(BigInt(nonce));\n  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer(), nonceBuf],\n    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Alternative Implementation** (test version): `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/coinflip.ts` (lines 71-82)\n\n```typescript\nfunction getMatchPda(\n  creator: PublicKey,\n  nonce: number | bigint = 0\n): PublicKey {\n  const nonceBuf = Buffer.alloc(8);\n  nonceBuf.writeBigUInt64LE(BigInt(nonce));\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer(), nonceBuf],\n    PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Program IDs\n\n**Coinflip Program ID**: `BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx`\n\n**Source**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/Anchor.toml` (lines 9, 15)\n- Localnet: `BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx`\n- Devnet: `BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx`\n\nAlso declared in: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/lib.rs` (line 9)\n```rust\ndeclare_id!(\"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\");\n```\n\n---\n\n### IDL Documentation\n\nThe IDL at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.ts` (lines 783) includes:\n```\n\"PDA seeds: [b\\\"match\\\", creator.key().as_ref(), &nonce.to_le_bytes()]\"\n```\n\nThis confirms the exact seed structure across both Rust and TypeScript implementations."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a387fbe03fe1be89c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 54728\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 63343</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f4316b62-2257-4469-b202-66365945525c","uuid":"26370fcd-d088-45eb-b94e-77d1f497b928","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and read the on-chain PDA derivation for CoinflipMatch. Look in:\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/` — find where the match PDA seeds are defined (should be `[\"match\", creator, nonce.to_le_bytes()]`)\n2. Find any existing TypeScript code that derives the same PDA (e.g., in anchor-client or test files)\n3. Check what the coinflip program ID is (in Anchor.toml or similar)\n\nReturn the exact seed format and any example TypeScript PDA derivation code.","agentId":"a387fbe03fe1be89c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information needed. Let me compile the findings:\n\n## CoinflipMatch PDA Derivation - Complete Reference\n\n### On-Chain Definition (Rust)\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs` (lines 18-19)\n\n```rust\n/// A coinflip match between two players (commit-reveal model).\n/// PDA seeds: [b\"match\", creator.key().